						<summary>

						<p>Third slab in the same place.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">No King: (Sarvajit) Āḍi 2.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is incomplete at the end. It mentions a certain Vīdiviṭaṅkanayiṉār who imposed a fresh tax on the <hi rend="italic">tānattār</hi> (trustees) inhabiting the premises of the temple of Aḻagiya-Tiruchchiṟṟaṁbalamuḍaiyāṉ in Koḻumam. The imprecatory passage at the end says that those who do not obey would be deemed to have wronged the deity Nittaniṉṟāḍuvār (i.e., Naṭarāja).</p>						

						</summary>
